# TECH REPORT 4

## 5G Technology

[This is the description] (https://www.qualcomm.com/5g/what-is-5g)
-  5G is the 5th generation mobile network. It is a new global wireless standard after 1G, 2G, 3G, and 4G networks.
- 5G enables a new kind of network that is designed to connect virtually everyone and everything together including machines, objects, and devices.


## 5G's key features and capabilities

(https://www.ericsson.com/en/5g)
- Faster speeds
- Massive connections
- Efficient coverage
- Wider bandwidths

(https://www.ibm.com/think/insights/5g-advantages-disadvantages)
- Advantages of 5G technology
 1. Smaller physical footprint
 2. Lower latencies

- Disadvantages of 5G
  1. Cybersecurity
  2. Gaps in coverage
